## üíé Product name

VR Racing Game

  

## üéØ Objective

The main goal of this project is to create a VR racing game that provides an immersive experience for gamers. The MVP will cater to gamers who own VR headsets and are looking for an exciting racing game.

  

## üî≠ Product scope

|In scope|Out of scope|
|---|---|
|Basic racing gameplay|Multiplayer mode|
|Single-player mode|Additional racetracks|
|Basic car customization|Advanced car customization|

  

## ü´∂ Value proposition

Offers gamers an immersive racing experience in the comfort of their own homes. With realistic graphics and responsive controls, players will feel like they're in the driver's seat.

  

## üß© Features & functionalities

|Feature name|Description|Priority|
|---|---|---|
|Basic racing gameplay|Drive, steer, accelerate, and brake|High|
|Single-player mode|Race against AI opponents|Medium|
|Basic car customization|Change paint colors and decals|Low|

  

## üéÆ User flow

Step 1: Select a racetrack

- User launches the Virtual Racer game on their VR headset.
- User navigates to the racetrack selection screen within the main menu.

Step 2: Customize your car

- User accesses the car customization options to change paint colors and apply decals.
- User chooses their preferred car appearance to make it unique.

Step 3: Race against AI opponents

- After selecting their car and racetrack, users start the race and engage in thrilling VR racing action.
- Users compete against AI opponents, maneuvering through twists and turns to reach the finish line.

Step 4: View race time on leaderboard

- Once the race is completed, the user's race time will be automatically recorded.
- Users can check the leaderboard to see how their time compares to other players.
